article.headline: Niagara 81, Manhattan 70
article.story: LEWISTON, N.Y. (AP) -- Charron Fisher scored 27 points to lead Niagara in an 81-70 win over Manhattan Friday. Clif Brown and Lorenzo Miles had 17 points apiece for Niagara (12-11 , 7-5 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference), while Tyrone Lewis added 13 points. Arturo Dubois had 25 points and 10 rebounds to led the Jaspers (11-11, 8-4). Darryl Crawford added 10 points for Manhattan. Niagara, which trailed by as many as eight points in the first half, led 38-34 at halftime. Never trailing in the second half, Niagara led by as many as 20 points. Lewis gave Niagara momentum going into intermission when he scored on a layup while being fouled with less than a second left. Brown had eight points to key a 19-4 Niagara run over a period of four minutes to give the Purple Eagles a 75-55 lead with less than five minutes to play. Niagara went 18-of-28 from the foul line, Manhattan was 3-of-8.
